# Docs Governance

- Keep README concise; place detailed policy in `docs/`.
- Use ADRs in `docs/adr/` for durable architecture decisions.
- Update `CHANGELOG.md` for user-visible changes and release notes.
- Keep `docs/roadmap.md` focused on phases, priorities, and open work.
- Link related docs instead of duplicating large sections.
- Avoid documenting generated local data as committed source.
